    {
      "id": "272bbacbc89d7d23aae3e0560c95d534a98f7ec0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2025-01-07 18:28:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nIt looks like the root of the problem was that *any* el9.3+x86_64 kernel build was having problems due to a missing openjdk package (which is needed to build the \"perf\" package for some reason), and this patch just masked the problem by not triggering a kernel build.\n\nThat said, I'm not against landing it (it is harmless to do so), since there are now several patches depending on it and they will be unlandable otherwise.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "15c33a608b08939cf3c0e52c20ff4708c9b657ed",
      "author": {
